          <div class=3D"w3-content w3-container w3-hide-small" id=3D"tempve=
rbiage">
            <p>A Temporary Rating may be provided by Chief handicapper in t=
he event a handicap is requested to race in an upcoming race which will tak=
e place before a meeting, and the board is unable to vote on the rating (Pr=
ior to race). The request should be email approved or voted on at next boar=
d meeting to make permanent. In the event at a board meeting where an owner=
 has submitted an application, fees are paid, but the Board believes it doe=
s not have sufficient data or information to accurately rate a boat, a Temp=
orary rating may be provided with the understanding the owner should submit=
 race results during the three months to show data, to verify the Temporary=
 Rating. Temporary rating may be adjusted after review of results. In the e=
vent the data is not provided the temporary rating will be considered expir=
ed at the end of 120 days. A new complete application (Minus Fees) will nee=
d to be presented to board to have the boat considered again for a PHRF cer=
tificate. The Chief Handicapper may, at his or her discretion, renew the Te=
mporary Rating twice.</p>
